    <string-array name="math_advanced_explanations">

        <!-- Explanation_1 -->
        <item>2x + 5 = 13 → 2x = 8 → x = 4.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_2 -->
        <item>Area = π r² = 3.14 × 49 = 153.86.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_3 -->
        <item>Find two numbers that multiply to 6 and add to 5: 2 and 3. So (x+2)(x+3).</item>

        <!-- Explanation_4 -->
        <item>In y = mx + b, m is the gradient. Here m = 3.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_5 -->
        <item>(4+7+9+12+8) / 5 = 40/5 = 8.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_6 -->
        <item>Pythagorean theorem: a² + b² = c² for right-angled triangles.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_7 -->
        <item>Multiply coefficients: 3×2=6. Add exponents: 2+3=5. Result: 6x⁵.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_8 -->
        <item>Sorted: 1,3,5,7,9. Middle value = 5.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_9 -->
        <item>Interior angle sum = (n-2)×180 = 4×180 = 720°.</item>

        <!-- Explanation_10 -->
        <item>x² = 9 → x = ±3.</item>

    </string-array>



